ABUJA – President Muhammadu Buhari has formally backed rotation of power to the Southern part of the country in the 2023 presidential election. The president made this known at a dinner with the All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential aspirants at the Aso Villa, in Abuja. Buhari’s decision came following an advisory by the APC Northern Governors that the President should zero his search for a successor to South. Among the APC presidential aspirants from the South who may top Buhari’s choice of successor are: Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, former Lagos governor, Bola Tinubu; former and Transportation Minister, Rotimi Amaechi; former science and technology minister, Ogbonnaya Onu and former minister of state (education), Emeka Nwajiuba. •Senate President Ahmad Lawan ABUJA - Governors and leaders from the Northern part of the country have dumped the idea of the President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan, standing for the 2023 presidency on the platform of All Progressive Congress, The Eagleonline reports The position of the Governors and Leaders… In "Top Stories" Dr Ogbonnaya Onu President to use Onu's choice to pacify the South East, will present him to other aspirants in matter of days | 'Rooting for Onu will be a masterstroke for country's unity at this time' By INNOCENT ODOH The minister of Science and Technology and Innovation, Dr. Ogbonnaya… In "Politics" By CHIJIOKE OKORONKWO ABUJA- Few days after President Muhammadu Buhari indicated a template for his successor in the forthcoming APC Presidential Primaries, governors of the ruling party are beginning to rally around Vice President Yemi Osinbajo who is believed to fit the president’s description.Several APC governors were sighted in the… In "Politics"